com.salesforce.omakase.plugin.conditionals

Class Conditionals

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.salesforce.omakase.plugin.conditionals.Conditionals
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DependentPlugin, Plugin

    public final class Conditionals
extends Object
implements DependentPlugin
    An extension to the standard CSS syntax that allows for conditional at-rules.

    Example of a conditional at-rule: 

      @if(ie7) { .test{color:red} }
    This block will output its inner statements if its condition matches one of the true conditions in the ConditionalsConfig instance.

    To enable conditionals, register an instance of this plugin during parser setup: 

     Conditionals conditionals = new Conditionals("ie7");
 Omakase.source(input).use(conditionals).process();

    For more information on using and configuring conditionals see the main readme file.

    See Also:
    ConditionalsConfig, ConditionalsCollector

      • dependencies

        public void dependencies(PluginRegistry registry)
        Description copied from interface: DependentPlugin
        Registers plugin dependencies.

        Any plugins you add to the registry in this method will be ordered before this plugin itself.

        Keep in mind that only one instance of a plugin can be added in a single parsing operation. You can use PluginRegistry.require(Class), PluginRegistry.require(Class, Supplier) and PluginRegistry.retrieve(Class) to assist in scenarios where a plugin instance may have already been added.

        Dependencies to include can range from refinement dependencies such as SelectorPlugin and MediaPlugin to other custom plugins.

        Specified by:
        dependencies in interface DependentPlugin
        Parameters:
        registry - The PluginRegistry instance.
        See Also:
        PluginRegistry.require(Class), PluginRegistry.require(Class, Supplier), PluginRegistry.retrieve(Class)
